==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plymouth Brethren
<hw>Plym"outh Breth"ren</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>The members of a
religious sect which first appeared at Plymouth, England, about 1830.
They protest against sectarianism, and reject all official ministry or
clergy. Also called <altname>Brethren</altname>, <altname>Christian
Brethren</altname>, <altname>Plymouthists</altname>, etc. The
<stype>Darbyites</stype> are a division of the Brethren.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pneometer</ent>⟦br⟧
